import StringIO
def show(p):

  img.seek(0)
  print "%html " + img.buf

%sql select t1.stn_number, t1.maxLat, t1.minLat, t1.maxLon, t1.minLon, round(deltaLat,2) as deltaLat, round(deltaLon,2) as deltaLon
from (select stn_number, max(latitude) as maxLat, min(latitude) as minLat, 
      max(longitude) as maxLon, min(longitude) as minLon,
      max(latitude)-min(latitude) as deltaLat, max(longitude)-min(longitude) as deltaLon 
      from rawDataTable 
      group by stn_number) t1
      where stn_number < 100
order by stn_number

print ("""%html <font color='brown'><h4> Notice the polyglot capabilities of Zeppelin and how easily the result of the SQL statement above can be reused as a new dataframe.<h4>""")
print ("""This dataframe can itself be registered as a new table, which will be named 'stations'.<h4>""")

result.msg: <font color='brown'><h4> Notice the polyglot capabilities of Zeppelin and how easily the result of the SQL statement above can be reused as a new dataframe.<h4>This dataframe can itself be registered as a new table, which will be named 'stations'.<h4>

paragraphs.title: Reuse the sQL statement above to create a new dataframe
paragraphs.text:
%pyspark 
stations = sqlContext.sql("""select t1.stn_number, t1.maxLat, t1.minLat, t1.maxLon, t1.minLon, t1.deltaLat, t1.deltaLon 
      from (select stn_number, max(latitude) as maxLat, min(latitude) as minLat, 
            max(longitude) as maxLon, min(longitude) as minLon,
            max(latitude)-min(latitude) as deltaLat, max(longitude)-min(longitude) as deltaLon 
            from rawDataTable 
            group by stn_number) t1
order by stn_number""")

map.plot(xs, ys, 'bo', markersize=15)
map.plot(xs2, ys2, 'rD', markersize=15)
map.plot(xs3, ys3, 'gD', markersize=15)

paragraphs.title: summer season: correlation of temperatures and salinities
paragraphs.text:
import org.apache.spark.mllib.stat.Statistics
val data = z.sqlContext.sql("""select minTemp, maxTemp, avgTemp, minSal, maxSal, avgSal, obs_year, Counts 
from (select min(temperature) as minTemp, max(temperature) as maxTemp, round(avg(temperature),2) as avgTemp, 
             min(salinity) as minSal, max(salinity) as maxSal, round(avg(salinity),2) as avgSal,
             obs_year, count(*) as Counts 
      from cleanDataTable where depth_press <= 10 
      and (obs_month >=6 and obs_month <=9)
      group by obs_year 
      order by obs_year) t1
where Counts >= 10 """)

val avgTemp = data.rdd.map(x=>x(2).asInstanceOf[Double])
val avgSal = data.rdd.map(x=>x(5).asInstanceOf[Double])
val correlation: Double = Statistics.corr(avgTemp, avgSal, "pearson")
